external_knowledge:
- Gardens represent applications;
- Flowers symbolize performance profiles;
- Gardeners planting and watering flowers refer to the creation and update of profiles by users;
- Bees visiting flowers are metaphors for access logs, indicating how many times a profile has been accessed;
- The health of flowers denotes performance metrics;
- The popularity of flowers in a garden is determined by the number of bee visits (access count);
- Each garden (application) has its own average number of bee visits (average access count);
- The rank of a flower (profile) is based on its bee visit count (access count), with the most visited being the most popular.
